00:36:38,495 --> 00:36:39,663
Can I come, too?

528
00:36:41,331 --> 00:36:43,333
Not yet.

529
00:36:51,258 --> 00:36:52,676
[SNORING]

530
00:37:06,857 --> 00:37:07,858
[GASPS]

531
00:37:07,941 --> 00:37:10,777
Hello! Is Casey Newton home?

532
00:37:11,028 --> 00:37:12,279
Uh, no.

533
00:37:12,446 --> 00:37:14,573
She ordered some cookies
and I’m delivering them.

534
00:37:15,532 --> 00:37:16,908
You’re a Girl Scout?

535
00:37:17,075 --> 00:37:18,367
Of course I am.

536
00:37:18,534 --> 00:37:20,036
Why aren’t you wearing a uniform?

537
00:37:20,202 --> 00:37:21,454
It’s at the cleaners.

538
00:37:21,621 --> 00:37:23,706
Those are Oreos.

539
00:37:25,875 --> 00:37:28,044
Could you please tell me
when Casey will be back?

540
00:37:28,377 --> 00:37:29,961
She went camping with some friends.

541
00:37:30,045 --> 00:37:32,047
She’s gonna be gone
for a couple of days.

542
00:37:32,213 --> 00:37:34,424
Is that what you’ve told your parents?

543
00:37:35,300 --> 00:37:36,301
Um...

544
00:37:36,384 --> 00:37:37,427
Yeah.

545
00:37:37,594 --> 00:37:38,720
But it’s not true.

546
00:37:38,887 --> 00:37:40,055
Yeah, it is.

547
00:37:40,221 --> 00:37:42,057
No, Nathan. It’s not.

548
00:37:42,557 --> 00:37:44,476
- [GASPS]
- Don’t ask me how I know your name.

549
00:37:44,643 --> 00:37:48,146
I know it the same way
I know that you are lying to me.

550
00:37:49,272 --> 00:37:51,148
Are you from the future?

551
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:53,609
You clearly understand.

552
00:37:53,776 --> 00:37:56,403
So why aren’t you telling me
what I need to know?

553
00:37:58,071 --> 00:38:00,782
That pin thing, it stopped working.

554
00:38:00,948 --> 00:38:02,742
She went to find another one.

555
00:38:02,909 --> 00:38:05,370
Nathan, where is she looking?

556
00:38:05,453 --> 00:38:07,080
[HONKING]

557
00:38:12,418 --> 00:38:14,170
<i>NEIL ARMSTRONG: [ON TV]
That’s one small step

558
00:38:14,253 --> 00:38:15,588
<i>for man...

559
00:38:15,755 --> 00:38:18,007
<i>- one giant leap for mankind.</i>
- [CHUCKLES]

560
00:38:29,102 --> 00:38:30,394
[EXPLOSIONS ON TV]

561
00:38:34,106 --> 00:38:35,273
CASEY: [CLEARS THROAT] Hello?

562
00:38:36,024 --> 00:38:38,110
Sale this week. Front three shelves.

563
00:38:38,527 --> 00:38:39,778
70% off.

564
00:38:39,945 --> 00:38:42,698
Oh, no, thanks.
I’m not here to buy anything. Um...

565
00:38:44,032 --> 00:38:46,451
I was hoping that
you could tell me about this.

566
00:38:50,997 --> 00:38:52,040
Hugo!

567
00:38:53,624 --> 00:38:54,834
Hugo!

568
00:38:55,209 --> 00:38:56,252
One second.

569
00:38:56,836 --> 00:38:57,962
[FAN FARE PLAYING]

570
00:38:58,129 --> 00:39:01,173
Welcome to <i>Blast From The...</i>
[GROANS]

571
00:39:01,674 --> 00:39:03,300
[MUSIC FADES]

572
00:39:04,468 --> 00:39:05,636
Thank you for the help, dear.

573
00:39:05,803 --> 00:39:07,471
Well, if you just kept it open,
you wouldn’t need my help.

574
00:39:07,638 --> 00:39:09,557
If I kept it open, it would ruin the effect,
which is everything.

575
00:39:09,640 --> 00:39:11,475
Pardon my wife.
She has no respect for showmanship.

576
00:39:11,642 --> 00:39:13,060
Hugo Gernsback. How may I help you?

577
00:39:13,144 --> 00:39:14,145
She has a pin.

578
00:39:15,563 --> 00:39:17,314
She has a pin.

579
00:39:17,690 --> 00:39:19,150
I saw that you were
looking for one online...

580
00:39:19,316 --> 00:39:20,860
Where did you get it?

581
00:39:21,026 --> 00:39:22,069
What can you tell me about it?

582
00:39:22,236 --> 00:39:24,405
I can’t tell you anything about it
unless you tell me who gave it to you.

583
00:39:24,572 --> 00:39:26,072
I’m not going first.

584
00:39:26,656 --> 00:39:27,782
[SIGHS]

585
00:39:27,866 --> 00:39:30,160
Well, it seems
our business here is done.

586
00:39:30,660 --> 00:39:32,746
It seems it is.

587
00:39:38,668 --> 00:39:40,670
HUGO: Saw something, didn’t you?

588
00:39:42,839 --> 00:39:44,674
When you touched it.

589
00:39:46,426 --> 00:39:48,845
Something incredible.

590
00:39:51,514 --> 00:39:52,724
It’s real?

591
00:39:52,891 --> 00:39:53,933
Of course it is.

592
00:39:54,100 --> 00:39:55,435
Don’t ask me how.

593
00:39:55,518 --> 00:39:56,936
These people have
developed technologies

594
00:39:57,020 --> 00:39:58,688
we haven’t even dreamed of yet.
[CHUCKLES]

595
00:39:58,855 --> 00:40:01,691
Wait. What people?

596
00:40:01,941 --> 00:40:02,942
Oh.

597
00:40:04,234 --> 00:40:05,444
[CHUCKLES]

598
00:40:06,361 --> 00:40:08,906
Have you ever wondered
what would happen

599
00:40:09,072 --> 00:40:13,577
if all the geniuses,
the artists, the scientists,

600
00:40:13,744 --> 00:40:16,705
the smartest,
most creative people in the world,

601
00:40:16,872 --> 00:40:19,708
decided to actually change it?

602
00:40:21,210 --> 00:40:22,920
But where?

603
00:40:23,086 --> 00:40:24,880
Where could they even do such a thing?

604
00:40:25,047 --> 00:40:28,383
They’d need a place
free from politics and bureaucracy,

605
00:40:28,550 --> 00:40:30,886
distractions, greed.

606
00:40:31,053 --> 00:40:34,222
A secret place where they could build

607
00:40:34,388 --> 00:40:37,141
whatever they were
crazy enough to imagine.

608
00:40:37,475 --> 00:40:40,228
“Plus Ultra” they call themselves.

609
00:40:40,394 --> 00:40:41,729
The only way to see it, however,

610
00:40:41,854 --> 00:40:44,482
is through contact with one of these.

611
00:40:44,649 --> 00:40:46,400
Why did they make them?
What are they for?

612
00:40:47,568 --> 00:40:48,986
Rumour has it

613
00:40:49,153 --> 00:40:51,239
- they were about to go public.
- HUGO: Yeah.

614
00:40:51,405 --> 00:40:53,741
Share what they had built
with the whole world.

615
00:40:53,908 --> 00:40:57,161
Unfortunately, that never happened.

616
00:40:58,287 --> 00:40:59,455
Why not?

617
00:41:00,289 --> 00:41:03,084
I think we’ve, uh,
shared enough, young lady.

618
00:41:04,043 --> 00:41:05,378
[CHUCKLES]

619
00:41:06,754 --> 00:41:09,131
So, um, as we’ve decided to trust you,

620
00:41:09,215 --> 00:41:11,133
please trust us

621
00:41:11,300 --> 00:41:13,761
and tell me, where’d you get it?

622
00:41:14,595 --> 00:41:15,763
Oh, uh...

623
00:41:15,847 --> 00:41:16,848
I don’t know.

624
00:41:17,640 --> 00:41:18,932
What do you mean, honey?

625
00:41:19,474 --> 00:41:20,517
Uh...

626
00:41:20,600 --> 00:41:23,854
I kind of got arrested
and it was in with my stuff.

627
00:41:24,312 --> 00:41:25,980
HUGO: In with your stuff?

628
00:41:26,146 --> 00:41:27,814
Yeah, I don’t know how it got there.

629
00:41:27,939 --> 00:41:29,107
[DOOR LOCKING]

630
00:41:30,441 --> 00:41:31,525
What was that?

631
00:41:31,692 --> 00:41:33,986
Tell us who gave it to you. Please.

632
00:41:34,152 --> 00:41:35,487
No one gave it to me!

633
00:41:37,447 --> 00:41:39,323
That’s very unlikely, sweetheart.

634
00:41:40,741 --> 00:41:42,994
Uh, you know what?

635
00:41:43,160 --> 00:41:45,120
I think I’m gonna go now.

636
00:41:45,287 --> 00:41:46,371
Thanks for your help.

637
00:41:47,205 --> 00:41:49,291
$1,000 if you tell me
where you acquired the pin.

638
00:41:49,457 --> 00:41:50,541
I don’t know!

639
00:41:50,624 --> 00:41:52,626
- $10,000.
- Was it a girl? A little girl?

640
00:41:52,793 --> 00:41:54,377
I don’t know
what you guys are talking about.

641
00:41:54,544 --> 00:41:56,504
Have a nice day. Enjoy your freak out.

642
00:41:57,714 --> 00:42:00,008
HUGO: Tell us where she is
and you will be spared.

643
00:42:02,135 --> 00:42:03,635
This is a joke, right?

644
00:42:03,719 --> 00:42:04,720
[GUN CHARGING]

645
00:42:04,803 --> 00:42:05,804
[SCREAMS]

646
00:42:09,725 --> 00:42:11,059
Where’s the girl?

647
00:42:12,643 --> 00:42:14,061
[SHUDDERING]

648
00:42:14,228 --> 00:42:16,564
I don’t... I don’t know about...

649
00:42:19,733 --> 00:42:20,984
[SIZZLES]

650
00:42:24,988 --> 00:42:26,406
- Ah!
- [GLASS SHATTERING]

651
00:42:27,532 --> 00:42:29,116
[LASER CHARGING]

652
00:42:31,701 --> 00:42:33,328
- [GROANS]
- [FLOOR CREAKING]

653
00:42:35,622 --> 00:42:36,623
[GUN BEEPING]

654
00:42:44,923 --> 00:42:46,049
- [TOY BEEPING]
- [GASPS]

655
00:42:47,759 --> 00:42:50,178
HUGO: You will tell us about the girl.

656
00:42:50,345 --> 00:42:51,679
I don’t know any girl.

657
00:42:51,846 --> 00:42:53,598
I told you... [STAMMERS]

658
00:42:53,765 --> 00:42:55,183
Where is the girl?

659
00:42:55,350 --> 00:42:57,018
I don’t know any girl!

660
00:42:57,101 --> 00:42:58,102
[GLASS SHATTERS]

661
00:43:06,319 --> 00:43:07,320
[GRUNTS]

662
00:43:10,198 --> 00:43:11,199
We have to go!

663
00:43:13,242 --> 00:43:14,744
Come on. Now!

664
00:43:16,120 --> 00:43:18,748
This is a time bomb.
It stops time, but not for long!

665
00:43:18,915 --> 00:43:21,042
- What?
- Listen to me.

666
00:43:21,209 --> 00:43:22,543
The sphere is collapsing

667
00:43:22,627 --> 00:43:24,712
and you’re in the line of fire.

668
00:43:24,879 --> 00:43:26,214
We need to go

669
00:43:26,381 --> 00:43:27,924
or you will die.

670
00:43:30,259 --> 00:43:31,719
[YELPS] I’m stuck!

671
00:43:32,303 --> 00:43:33,387
I’m stuck!

672
00:43:33,553 --> 00:43:34,972
But only temporarily.

673
00:43:35,138 --> 00:43:36,890
Take my hand.
The moment you’re free...

674
00:43:37,057 --> 00:43:38,392
I’ll pull you clear.

675
00:43:38,558 --> 00:43:39,934
Then stay behind me.

676
00:43:40,267 --> 00:43:41,310
Ready?

677
00:43:51,362 --> 00:43:52,654
[GRUNTING]

678
00:43:56,324 --> 00:43:57,325
[GRUNTS]

679
00:43:58,409 --> 00:43:59,410
The girl.

680
00:44:06,250 --> 00:44:07,251
[GRUNTS]

681
00:44:08,711 --> 00:44:09,795
[GROANS]

682
00:44:10,421 --> 00:44:11,422
[GLASS SHATTERS]

683
00:44:19,596 --> 00:44:20,680
- [GROANS]
- [METAL CLANGS]

684
00:44:25,101 --> 00:44:26,227
- [GRUNTS]
- [METAL CLANGS]

685
00:44:26,894 --> 00:44:27,895
[GRUNTS]

686
00:44:31,149 --> 00:44:32,150
[YELLS]

687
00:44:32,775 --> 00:44:33,776
- [GROANS]
- [CLANGING]

688
00:44:34,610 --> 00:44:35,611
[GRUNTS]

689
00:44:36,987 --> 00:44:37,988
Ah!

690
00:44:38,864 --> 00:44:39,948
Look out!

691
00:44:40,073 --> 00:44:41,074
[TOY BEEPING]

692
00:44:41,199 --> 00:44:42,200
[YELLING]

693
00:44:50,375 --> 00:44:51,459
We have to go.

694
00:44:52,293 --> 00:44:54,962
They’re about to self-destruct.
We have to go now!

695
00:44:56,005 --> 00:44:57,715
[REPEATING]
Crazy enough to imagine.

696
00:44:57,798 --> 00:44:59,466
Crazy enough to imagine.

697
00:45:04,304 --> 00:45:05,804
[CAR ALARMS BEEPING]

698
00:45:06,305 --> 00:45:07,306
[GASPS]

699
00:45:07,639 --> 00:45:08,723
[YELPS]

700
00:45:11,642 --> 00:45:13,394
Casey, get up.

701
00:45:13,561 --> 00:45:15,021
They’ll be coming.

702
00:45:15,188 --> 00:45:16,980
CASEY: What? Who?

703
00:45:20,317 --> 00:45:22,152
- I don’t know what... I can’t get into...
- I know, I know.

704
00:45:22,319 --> 00:45:23,987
Get in the car, Casey!

705
00:45:25,489 --> 00:45:27,073
How do you know my name?

706
00:45:27,490 --> 00:45:29,158
Just get in the car.

707
00:45:35,664 --> 00:45:36,707
[BEEPING]

708
00:45:36,791 --> 00:45:37,833
[ENGINE STARTS]

709
00:45:43,714 --> 00:45:44,840
What just happened?

710
00:45:44,924 --> 00:45:47,343
Two AA units targeted you
for extermination.

711
00:45:47,510 --> 00:45:49,845
I saved your life. They self-destructed.

712
00:45:50,012 --> 00:45:51,013
Wait. “AAs”?

713
00:45:51,514 --> 00:45:52,765
Audio-Animatronics.

714
00:45:52,932 --> 00:45:54,183
They were robots?

715
00:45:54,350 --> 00:45:57,019
No. Advanced anthropomo...

716
00:45:59,688 --> 00:46:01,190
Sure. Okay. Robots.

717
00:46:01,273 --> 00:46:02,733
[STAMMERS]

718
00:46:03,192 --> 00:46:05,027
Wait, wait. Who are you?

719
00:46:05,861 --> 00:46:09,281
My name is Athena.
I’m the one who gave you the pin.

720
00:46:09,615 --> 00:46:11,742
The pin? Oh, the pin!

721
00:46:11,909 --> 00:46:14,245
Yes. And I do wish you hadn’t run off

722
00:46:14,411 --> 00:46:17,289
before I had a chance to give you
some rather necessary context.

723
00:46:17,456 --> 00:46:19,708
Context?
What are you even talking about?

724
00:46:19,875 --> 00:46:22,586
How are you driving a car?
Who are you?

725
00:46:22,920 --> 00:46:24,880
I’m a <i>cruder.

726
00:46:25,297 --> 00:46:26,423
<i>[DISTORTED] Re...

727
00:46:26,549 --> 00:46:27,757
<i>I’m a...

728
00:46:27,924 --> 00:46:29,716
<i>[HIGH-PITCHED VOICE] recruton.

729
00:46:29,842 --> 00:46:31,093
[SIGHS]

730
00:46:36,557 --> 00:46:38,267
<i>MALE AUTOMATED VOICE:
60 seconds to self-destruct.

731
00:46:38,392 --> 00:46:39,393
[CRANKING]

732
00:46:43,188 --> 00:46:44,189
[CLICKS]

733
00:46:44,273 --> 00:46:46,108
So sorry about that.

734
00:46:46,275 --> 00:46:48,735
You’re one of them?

735
00:46:49,278 --> 00:46:50,612
Obviously.

736
00:46:53,907 --> 00:46:55,117
[BRAKES SCREECHING]

737
00:46:58,245 --> 00:46:59,496
Where are you going?

738
00:46:59,663 --> 00:47:01,957
Stop! I’m trying to help you!

739
00:47:02,124 --> 00:47:03,458
[BRAKES SCREECHING]

740
00:47:03,959 --> 00:47:04,960
[GASPS]

741
00:47:08,172 --> 00:47:09,798
Oh, my God. Oh, my God!

742
00:47:23,270 --> 00:47:24,313
Hey!

743
00:47:25,772 --> 00:47:26,773
Hey!

744
00:47:26,899 --> 00:47:28,358
[WHIRRING]

745
00:47:36,617 --> 00:47:39,703
This isn’t happening.
This isn’t happening.

746
00:47:42,623 --> 00:47:44,041
No way!

747
00:47:46,210 --> 00:47:47,211
- [SCREAMING]
- [BRAKES SCREECHING]

748
00:47:48,670 --> 00:47:50,005
[SCREAMING]

749
00:47:55,886 --> 00:47:57,137
Let me out of this car!

750
00:47:57,304 --> 00:47:58,639
Stop yelling!

751
00:47:58,764 --> 00:48:00,182
- Let me out now!
- No!

752
00:48:00,349 --> 00:48:01,391
I will not!

753
00:48:01,558 --> 00:48:03,769
I gave you my very last pin, young lady,

754
00:48:03,852 --> 00:48:05,979
and I am not about to let it go to waste.

755
00:48:06,146 --> 00:48:08,148
What do you mean your last pin?

756
00:48:11,818 --> 00:48:14,655
Wait, that place I saw...

757
00:48:17,157 --> 00:48:18,325
It exists?

758
00:48:18,492 --> 00:48:20,035
Of course it does.

759
00:48:20,827 --> 00:48:22,787
But if you don’t come with me,

760
00:48:22,870 --> 00:48:24,497
it won’t for much longer.

761
00:48:26,040 --> 00:48:27,041
Why not?

762
00:48:27,208 --> 00:48:29,000
Because they built something
they shouldn’t have.

763
00:48:30,168 --> 00:48:32,003
Built what?

764
00:48:32,337 --> 00:48:34,005
Do you want to
keep asking me questions

765
00:48:34,089 --> 00:48:35,757
until someone arrives to murder us?

766
00:48:35,882 --> 00:48:36,925
No.

767
00:48:37,384 --> 00:48:40,387
Then which way do you want to go?

768
00:48:40,553 --> 00:48:44,266
Backwards, or forwards?

769
00:48:45,517 --> 00:48:47,017
And you can take me there?

770
00:48:47,351 --> 00:48:48,352
I can.

771
00:48:48,686 --> 00:48:50,020
[SIGHS]

772
00:48:52,022 --> 00:48:53,065
I’m driving.

773
00:48:53,607 --> 00:48:55,025
[POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

774
00:48:55,109 --> 00:48:56,110
Okie-dokie.

775
00:48:56,277 --> 00:48:57,945
You fellas are released. Thanks.

776
00:48:59,613 --> 00:49:01,031
Alrighty, boys.

777
00:49:02,866 --> 00:49:05,869
Fire chief says we’re clear
to go in and poke around.

778
00:49:06,036 --> 00:49:07,412
Hopefully they were out for lunch

779
00:49:07,495 --> 00:49:09,580
and nobody was in there
when she went boom.

780
00:49:09,747 --> 00:49:10,790
DEPUTY 1: Captain.

781
00:49:16,421 --> 00:49:17,422
Afternoon, sir.

782
00:49:17,588 --> 00:49:19,132
Dave Clark, Secret Service.

783
00:49:19,215 --> 00:49:21,009
- [DOG WHINING]
- [CHUCKLES] Ooh.

784
00:49:21,384 --> 00:49:22,385
[BARKS]

785
00:49:22,593 --> 00:49:24,553
Looks like you got yourself a doozy here.

786
00:49:24,720 --> 00:49:26,096
Secret Service?

787
00:49:26,263 --> 00:49:27,389
Hey, where are they going?

788
00:49:27,472 --> 00:49:28,556
They’re securing the premises.

789
00:49:28,723 --> 00:49:30,266
Thanks so much for your help,

790
00:49:30,349 --> 00:49:32,059
but we’re going to take it from here.

791
00:49:33,477 --> 00:49:34,478
DEPUTY 2: Hey, Dale.

792
00:49:34,562 --> 00:49:37,231
I found this just outside the window.

